==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filanders
<hw>Fil"an*ders</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>filandres</ets>, fr. L. <ets>filum</ets> thread.]</ety>
<fld>(Falconry)</fld> <def>A disease in hawks, characterized by the
presence of small threadlike worms, also of filaments of coagulated
blood, from the rupture of a vein; -- called also
<altname>backworm</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filar</ent>⟦br⟧
